<!--
VOICING PLAN:
- Key F, 4/4. Short 8-bar evening prayer. "33" root triads primary.
- E (ABC "^E" in bar 6 melody) = natural E, diatonic in F. Harp treats as C (⑤).
- Dm = ④m at bar 8. Bb = ④. C7 = ⑤7. Am = ③m. All diatonic.
- LH: 4-note open throughout. RH: 2-note thirds/sixths.

VOICE LEADING HIGHLIGHTS:
- Repeated C-F-C rocking in LH bars 1-4 anchors the tonic.
- Bar 7: F→Dm→C7→F step in LH (F2→D2→C2→F2) — classic cadential bass movement.
- Contrary motion bar 7-8: RH descends G5-E5 while LH rises D2-F2.

TEXTURE ARC:
- Quiet and simple throughout. Opens bars 1-4 with sustained F-C ostinato in LH.
- Bars 5-8 slightly more harmonically varied (Bb, C7 added). Final F cadence clear.
-->
